# Concepts

Canonical vocabulary for the local Pi review-document system.

## Pi Note

A local review document generated from or opened by a Pi session. A Pi Note can be read like a static page but can also send review turns back to its spawning Pi session.

## Product Namespace

A stable slug that scopes notes, routes, source files, assets, and bridge state for one product or project.

## Review Document

A typography-first page for inspecting generated material and giving precise feedback. It should support keyboard navigation, block selection, comments, rewrites, and batch sends.

## Document Host

The local SvelteKit/mdsvex server that renders reviewable documents. It provides routes, assets, theme defaults, adapter loading, and bridge endpoints.

## Document Adapter

A project-specific module that teaches the Document Host how to load, parse, render, and address one document family.

It may ingest `.mdx`, `.svx`, `.md`, JSON, or database-backed documents.

## Brain Data

Large or structured source material stored under `.brain/data/**` and rendered by project-local Brain components.

Brain Data keeps `.svx` pages small and narrative while letting the Document Host render thousands of source-backed records without feeding raw source text through MDSvX.

## Brain Component

A project-local Svelte renderer under `.brain/components/**/*.svelte`.

Brain Components are auto-imported by tag name in `.svx` pages. They should own pagination, virtualization, lazy media, and safe text rendering for `.brain/data/**` records.

## Spawned Session

The Pi session that created the review document. The session identity is the default routing target for feedback batches.

## Pi Bridge

The local bridge between browser review UI and the spawned Pi session. It accepts feedback batches, sends them to Pi as user turns, and emits status and document-change events back to the browser.

## Local Site Actor

A lifecycle-managed process that serves product-namespaced review documents locally. It starts, advertises a stable portless route, watches files, and shuts down on Pi session shutdown.

## Source Subtree

A shallow, vendored source snapshot under `repos/` used as local reference material. It is not a runtime dependency and must be excluded from TypeScript, SvelteKit, Vite, and formatting scans.

## Review Turn

A feedback payload sent from a review document into Pi as a user message. Review turns may include selected block ids, current text, comments, requested rewrites, and global instructions.

## Document Event Stream

SSE/WebSocket stream from the local site to the browser. It reports bridge status, Pi turn status, file changes, reload hints, and errors.

## Keyboard Review Surface

The browser UI layer inspired by keystrok: minimal chrome, strong focus states, command palette or key hints, and predictable keyboard movement.

## Support Page

A product adapter surface for support operations. It can render queue cards, review packs, customer/context evidence, or draft replies while sending operator comments back into Pi as Review Turns.

## Build Capture

A durable note about the build process: decision, insight, gotcha, code change, concept, risk, or next step. Captures start as gremlin entries but must graduate into focused Brain topics.

## Course-Like Build

A product build treated as teachable source material. Agents preserve not just code, but the concepts, tradeoffs, workflow, and validation path needed to reconstruct the work later.

## pi-notes Knowledge Rig

The future replacement for Brain in this project: customizable mdsvex/Svelte knowledge pages with graph validation and active Pi-session feedback.

## Agent-Loop Graph

A local knowledge graph where agents capture, propose, review, merge, and validate graph changes as part of normal Pi session work.

## Graph Edge

A typed or inferred relationship between nodes, blocks, source files, decisions, concepts, receipts, or review items.

## Block Reference

A Roam-inspired reference to a specific block-level unit of knowledge, useful for backlinks, review comments, and precise agent edits.
